---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PassportFooter from '../components/PassportFooter.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Reconstructor's Foreword">
  <div class="story-header">
    <a href="/" class="back-link mono-block">← INDEX</a>
  </div>

  <h1 class="sr-only">Reconstructor's Foreword</h1>

  <article class="prose-column">
    <p><em>To be written.</em></p>

    <p>
      A brief note, no more than two or three paragraphs, in the
      reconstructor's voice. It introduces the archive without explaining
      it. It does not name the reconstructor. It does not say which
      government, which decade after, which institution allowed (or refused)
      access. It is professional and short.
    </p>

    <p>
      The reader should finish it slightly unsure what kind of document
      they are about to read, and slightly more willing to find out.
    </p>
  </article>

  <PassportFooter />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .story-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .back-link {
    color: var(--color-faint);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .back-link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    .back-link {
      color: var(--color-faint-dark);
    }
  }
</style>
